                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d490">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rumley</persName>, collector, to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Boutwell</persName>, Secretary of the Treasury.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilmington, North Carolina</hi>
                    </placeName>,<lb/>
                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-10-07">
                        <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 7, 1869</date>.</dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Geo. S. Boutwell</hi>, <hi
                        rend="italic">Secretary of Treasury:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <seg type="margin">[172]</seg> Should I fail to make good the allegation against
                    the Lady Sterling on Monday next, I fear an attempt will *be made to escape and
                    put to sea. The captain is unwilling for me to place an officer on board, and
                    the force at my command is entirely inadequate to thwart any movement of that
                    kind. Can you furnish me with an armed cutter at once?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>D. RUMLEY,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Collector.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
